AWS Systems Manager Agent (SSM Agent) is Amazon software that can be installed and configured on an EC2 instance, an on-premises server, or a virtual machine (VM).
SSM Agent makes it possible for Systems Manager to update, manage, and configure these resources.
AWS Systems Manager Agent (SSM Agent) is an AWS service that you can use to view and control your infrastructure on AWS.
Supporting OS type includes window server, multiple distributions of linux.
Create a role for target EC2 instance service with an policy as "AmazonEC2RoleforSSM".